  m_Name: beetle
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::WordInfo
  word: beetle
  info: '<color="blue">Beetles</color> are a part of the largest animal kingdom orders,
    <color="blue">Coleoptera</color>. The life cycle of a typical beetle starts with
    an <color="blue">egg</color> stage. Once hatched, the <color="blue">larva</color>
    stage begins. The <color="blue">larva</color> will eat and grow eventually turning
    into a <color="blue">pupa</color> where they will be immobile, typically during
    the winter months. In the spring, the <color="blue">adult beetle</color> will
    emerge and continue the cycle by feeding, mating, and laying eggs.


    Source:
    https://www.webmd.com/a-to-z-guides/beetles-what-to-know '
